I've known that for a long time.

221
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:19,154
No. You love me,
and I love you.

222
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,879
<i>You</i> love you.
<i>I</i> love Walter.

223
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:27,159
-Will you stop saying that?
-Max, it's over for us. Over.

224
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:30,391
All right.
Then just go to bed with me.

225
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,357
<i>[Ping-Pong Ball</i>
<i>Bouncing]</i>

226
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:35,477
<i>A few of the Maestro's things.</i>
<i>He moves back in today, you know.</i>

227
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:39,075
Yeah, I know. Party's over for you guys.
You'll have to go home.

228
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,355
Some girl called.
Said she'd taken a lot of pills...

229
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,556
and was gonna kill herself
if you didn't call her.

230
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,710
<i>[Walter] No, no. I get those calls</i>
<i>two or three times a week.</i>

231
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,631
-She really sounds bad.
-<i>[Doorbell Buzzing]</i>

232
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:51,235
I think she sounds awful,
but she sold six million records last year.

233
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,956
-Walter!
-Hey, how are ya?

234
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,838
I gotta get some food
right now!

235
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:06,433
Okay, we promised never to come to your
place again, but this is a major crisis.

236
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,351
It's not my place
any more.

237
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:11,750
When your father took all our money,
you were so nice to us.

238
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,434
-You washed my hair.
I didn't forget that.
-<i>## [Piano]</i>

239
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,715
We trust you.
We need your advice.

240
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:19,189
I am sure I did not
wash your hair.

241
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,589
Look, I gotta get up early
tomorrow and go see Benny.

242
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,511
-You see Benny?
-<i>[Man] He sees Benny?</i>

243
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,319
-What's your problem?
-We want to change the name of the band.

244
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,789
You can't do that!
You've spent years and a fortune...

245
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,711
to make your name
a household word.

246
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,439
Your name is perfect.
"Cheap Girls." I love it.

247
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:36,557
-I'm not sure it's us.
-<i>[Burps]</i>
-It is.

248
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:39,552
-We wanna call ourselves "Meryl Streep."
-<i>[Man Shouting]</i>

249
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:43,155
No, no. You cannot call yourselves
"Meryl Streep."

250
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,993
-<i>Maybe she'll be flattered.</i>
-No, in fact, considering your act...

251
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,991
I think I can guarantee
a giant lawsuit.

252
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,275
-<i>## [Piano Continues]</i>
-<i>[Clattering]</i>

253
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:52,191
Don't take off your coat.
Forget it.

254
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,396
You are not calling yourselves
"Meryl Streep."

255
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:57,438
-Come on, we're gonna go see a house.
-A house? Where?

256
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,556
An hour away
from everyone.

257
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:01,517
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>How about "Debbie Reynolds'"?</i>

258
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,989
Thanks very much.
Keep the change.

259
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:14,638
-This can't be it.
-It's the address.

260
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,834
<i>[Anna]</i>
<i>It's beautiful.</i>

261
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:21,434
I know.
Somethin' must be wrong.

262
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,512
Well, let's go see.

263
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:29,597
-Hi! Come on in.
-<i>[Anna] Thank you.</i>

264
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,069
<i>## [Classical]</i>

265
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:35,197
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

266
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:37,111
Mmm.

267
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:41,153
Excuse the way
the place looks.

268
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,038
I really let it go to hell
since Carlos left.

269
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:47,317
But the house
is beautiful.

270
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:50,517
Carlos and I
were very happy here.

271
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:53,353
It's all over now.
The living room's in here.

272
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:56,432
-This is great.
-Fabulous.

273
00:14:56,520 --> 00:15:00,115
<i>Listen, if you want</i>
<i>any of the furniture, it's all for sale.</i>

274
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:03,590
Well, I think that we'd like
to decorate it ourselves.

275
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:07,468
I'd sell it cheap.
I need all the money I can get.

276
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:10,791
Goddam bloodsucking lawyers
are bleeding me dry.

277
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:13,155
[Chuckling]

278
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,915
The floor just needs a little polish.
The bedroom's up here.

279
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:23,675
I'm trying to save a few bucks on the
lights... for the bloodsucking lawyers.

280
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:26,752
-<i>I think it's lovely.</i>
-<i>[Stairs Creaking]</i>

