and then one day...

300
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:34,752
Israeli Intelligence
comes to the door.

301
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,671
Israeli Intelligence?

302
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:41,515
Last Tuesday.
That's why I've gotta sell the house.

303
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:45,639
It turns out,
Carlos was Hitler's pool man.

304
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:50,198
-<i>[Toilet Flushing]</i>
-Mm-hmm.

305
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,597
Ouch!

306
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,956
There's a lot of grounds,
but the maintenance isn't too bad.

307
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:06,919
-I've always done it myself,
but you could hire a gardener.
-"A gardener"? No, no.

308
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,389
I could handle this.
This'd be a piece of cake.

309
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,596
[Anna]
Really?

310
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:15,672
[Car Horn Honking]

311
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,512
-<i>[Brakes Screeching]</i>
-<i>[Anna] Fabulous car!</i>

312
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,431
-What's it called again?
-It's a Lincoln.

313
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:21,556
-They don't make 'em like this any more.
-It's a beauty.

314
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,313
Do you like it? I'll throw it in
if you buy the house.

315
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,391
That's very generous.

316
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:29,040
I'm desperate.
Can we close?

317
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:31,270
Well, we need
a little time to...

318
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,749
There isn't any time.
Extradition is Friday.

319
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:36,912
-Extradition?
-I'll tell you later.

320
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,356
-I need an answer
by close of business tomorrow.
-<i>[Walter] Oh, you'll have it.</i>

321
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:45,275
By the way, you have the most
beautifully kept pool I've ever seen.

322
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:48,636
Oh, God. Oh, God.
[Weeping]

323
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:51,188
[Walter]
What did I say?

324
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,271
What did I say?

325
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:57,957
Jack was right.
We can't lose.

326
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:01,749
-Nothing can be this easy.
-Sure it can. You know what this is?

327
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:06,277
-This is the short line
in Motor Vehicles.
-What?

328
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:08,316
You go to Motor Vehicles
to get your licence renewed...

329
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,755
and you get on this line
that reaches to Spain.

330
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:13,718
And right next to it is this little
short line with only two guys on it.

331
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:16,792
But you don't get on that line, 'cause you
think something must be wrong with it...

332
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:20,031
otherwise everybody else would be
on it, so you waste three hours.

333
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:23,908
I got on the short line once.
It was for farm vehicles.

334
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,471
I want this house. I need this house.
We need this house.

335
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:31,996
-Could be great.
-Say "yes"!

336
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,390
If we do this,
we do it together.

337
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:40,472
I'm putting in half the money,
or I'm not going in.

338
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:44,394
-Great!
-I thought you'd give me an argument.

339
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:48,951
If I had any money, I would.
Where are you gonna get your half?

340
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,951
Max.

341
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:54,589
<i>I'll sell him everything I got in</i>
<i>the divorce. What about your half?</i>

342
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:57,956
I'm goin' straight to the top on this
one... Billboard's Artist of the Year.

343
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:01,919
-<i>He, who last year alone</i>
<i>sold 22 million records.</i>
-Benny?

344
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,514
-Yeah.
-<i>Benny himself?</i>

345
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:08,752
-<i>[Train Horn Blaring]</i>
-Did you hear that?

346
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:12,196
The train is coming, right when
we decided to buy the house!

347
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:14,669
-<i>[Train Horn Blaring Continues]</i>
-This has got to be an omen.

348
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:18,116
I can feel it! This is it!
Everything's breaking for us!

349
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:31,959
<i>## [TVCartoon]</i>

350
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,071
You say you have
an appointment?

351
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:37,913
I don't <i>say</i> I have
an appointment, I <i>have</i> an appointment!

352
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,831
-Hi, Mr Fielding.
-Hello.

353
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:42,639
-<i>[Boy] What the hell does he want?</i>
-<i>[Man] I don't know.</i>

354
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:45,518
<i>[Boy] Didn't you ask him? What's</i>
<i>the matter, I gotta pay you to think?</i>

355
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:48,398
<i>[Man] Hejust told me he wants</i>
<i>to see you. Sorry, Benny.</i>

356
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:51,790
<i>Oh, well, that makes everything better.</i>
<i>Walter, how are ya?</i>

357
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:57,469
Okay, you've seen me. Is that it,
or do you wanna talk too?

358
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,391
I wanna talk.

359
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,630
Figures.

360
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:04,757
<i>[TV] Now I'll show you how easy</i>
<i>I can catch a woodpecker.</i>

361
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:07,912
All right.
You've got five minutes.

362
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,036
<i>Are you gonna</i>
<i>let her do that?</i>

363
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,475
Are you gonna let my mother
clean that carpet?

364
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:16,793
-Thanks, Benny.
-Don't mention it.

365
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:19,269
-<i>I made a nice pot roast.</i>
-Don't mention that either.

366
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,430
[Chuckling]
He never eats.

367
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:25,308
<i>Look, Mom, we're real busy here.</i>
<i>Why don't you go watch TV?</i>

368
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,870
Hey, keep it brief.
I got a chick waiting in the Jacuzzi.

369
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:32,396
I wish I had
a hundred more like him.

370
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:37,598
There is a house
I want to buy.

371
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:41,150
<i>Let's just cut to the chase, okay?</i>
<i>What do you want?</i>

372
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:45,518
I want you to loan me
$200,000 in cash.

373
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,999
No.

374
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,032
-Benny!
-[Weapon Clicks]

375
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:52,475
-You shout at me?
-<i>I shout at you!</i>

376
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,471
I need that money,
and you're gonna loan it to me!

377
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:57,518
-I will not! No! No! No!
-<i>Yes, you will.</i>

378
00:20:57,600 --> 00:21:01,275
Yes, you will! I saved you
ten times that in taxes last year!

379
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:05,558
-So what?
-Benny, if you don't
loan me that money, I'll...

380
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:10,191
-You'll what, huh? You'll what?
-I'll not like you any more!

381
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:12,874
<i>[TVContinues]</i>

382
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:19,999
-All right.
-Thanks.

383
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:23,591
-<i>[Telephone Ringing]</i>
-[Jack] Great!

384
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,716
-<i>Great!</i>
-<i>[Telephone Hangs Up]</i>

385
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:28,075
-<i>They bought it! All right, gang!</i>
-<i>[Cheering, Applauding]</i>

386
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,991
Way to go!
[Coughing]

387
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,799
<i>-[Beeping]</i>
<i>-Not again.</i>

388
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:35,749
<i>## [Pop]</i>

389
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:41,920
<i># Anyplace you would be #</i>

